    <item>
      <title>My Neovim Setup</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/software-development/my-neovim-setup/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2026 20:11:33 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/software-development/my-neovim-setup/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;what-the-heck-even-is-neovim&#34;&gt;What the heck even is Neovim?&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I found about about Vim and Neovim through the Primeagen Youtube channel. Vim itself is an old text editor, and it works on the concept of buffers and various shortcuts called &amp;ldquo;motions&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I was intrigued as I saw Primeagen doing some really cool stuff with it, using sequences of motions to do complicated edits on files which would normally require the use of a mouse and/or some scripting.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
